 To find the polygon's number of sides, we use the formula for the interior angles of a polygon: $180(n - 2) = (n)x$. Here, $x$ is the interior angle of the polygon, $180(n - 2)$ is the total sum of interior angles, and $n$ is the number of sides of the polygon. We know the interior angle is $140^\circ$, so we have:

\begin{align*}
180(n - 2) &= nx \\
180n - nx &= 360 \\
n(180 - x) &= 360 \\
n &= \frac{360}{180 - x}
\end{align*}

Since $x = 140^\circ$, we can substitute this value into the equation:

\begin{align*}
n &= \frac{360}{180 - 140} \\
n &= \frac{360}{40} \\
n &= 9
\end{align*}

</think> So, the interior angle is calculated as $180(n-2)=nx \implies n = \frac{180(n-2)}{x}$ and the solution is $n=\boxed{9}$.

