\begin{align*} \frac{4+3c}{7}+2&=\frac{4+3c}{7}+\frac{2}{1}\\ &=\frac{4+3c}{7}+\frac{2\times7}{7\times1}&\text{[Getting a common denominator]}\\\\ &=\frac{4+3c}{7}+\frac{14}{7}&\text{[Multiplying and simplifying]}\\\\ &=\frac{4+3c+14}{7}&\text{[Adding]}\\\\ &=\frac{18+3c}{7}&\end{align*}
So our answer is $ \frac{18+3c}{7} $.</think> <answer> $\boxed{\frac{18+3c}{7}}$ </answer>
